# README for default-service

This service was scaffolded using MDScript.
Language: Deno
Stack: raw server, none messaging, no database
Deployment Target: Docker Compose
Health Endpoint: yes

## Getting Started

1. Clone the repository: `git clone <repo_url>`
2. Navigate to the directory: `cd default-service`
3. Build and run: `docker compose up --build`
// main entrypoint for default-service using Deno
Deno.serve((req) => {
  console.log("Service started.");

  if (req.url.includes("/health")) {
    return new Response(JSON.stringify({ status: "ok" }), { headers: { "Content-Type": "application/json" } });
  }

  // Main service logic here...
  return new Response("Hello, world!");
});
